    h1 Grid

    article
      h1 Fluid columns

      p Adding .row to a container will make all the children of that container behave like block elements.
      p There is no limit on the number of columns

      .demo
        each _, i in Array(16)
          +rowWithColumns(i+1)

    article
      h1 Fixed columns

      p Adding .col-NUMBER will make the column use a fixed width.
      p The default number of columns is 12

      .demo
        each _, i in Array(12)
          .row
            div(class=`col-${i+1}`)
              | col-#{i+1}

    article
      h1 Row Wrap

      h2 Default
      p The default is now to wrap the columns in the row.
      p The content will overflow the row and be visible
      .demo
        .row
          .col-5 1 .col-5
          .col-5 2 .col-5
          .col-5 3 .col-5

      h2 Force wrap / break
      p Adding `wrap-yes` will force the columns to break if they dont fit the row
      .demo
        .row.wrap-yes
          .col-5 1 .col-5
          .col-5 2 .col-5
          .col-5 3 .col-5

      h2 No wrap / break
      p Adding `wrap-no` will force the columns to not break, reseting back to the default behavior
      .demo
        .row.wrap-no
          .col-5 1 .col-5
          .col-5 2 .col-5
          .col-5 3 .col-5

      h2 Force wrap reverse / break reverse
